</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="505" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="21.[125,1334,282,950]" pageId="21" pageNumber="505">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[127,481,794,827]" pageId="21" pageNumber="505">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Least Concern on The [UCN Red List. Because Davis’s Round-eared Bats are sensitive to habitat disturbance by humans and have a relatively small distribution, they have been federally listed as threatened in 
<collectingCountry box="[1196,1301,873,906]" name="Mexico" pageId="21" pageNumber="505">Mexico</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
